Maddie, dancing to "Helen Keller."

00:38:49.694 --> 00:38:51.696 line:5%,start
(cheering and applause)

00:38:53.364 --> 00:38:56.701 line:95%,end
ABBY: Thank goodness
that Mackenzie pulled out a win

00:38:56.767 --> 00:38:58.002 line:95%,end
in her age division.

00:38:58.069 --> 00:38:59.603 line:95%,end
<i>Who knew the kid had it in her.</i>

00:38:59.670 --> 00:39:01.872 line:95%,end
But fourth and ninth?

00:39:01.939 --> 00:39:03.307 line:95%,end
I'm not happy about that.

00:39:03.374 --> 00:39:04.709 line:95%,end
(cheering)

00:39:05.943 --> 00:39:07.712 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Oh, good job!

00:39:07.778 --> 00:39:09.046 line:95%,end
MELISSA: I'm so proud of you!

00:39:09.113 --> 00:39:11.115 line:95%,end
-CHRISTI: And I'll hug Nia.
-MELISSA: I love it!

00:39:11.182 --> 00:39:13.050 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: Good job, Kenz!

00:39:13.417 --> 00:39:14.518 line:95%,end
I don't know what to think.

00:39:14.885 --> 00:39:17.154 line:95%,end
KELLY: Now that the competition
is done and over with,

00:39:17.221 --> 00:39:18.823 line:95%,end
I want to go give Abby a piece of my mind.

00:39:18.889 --> 00:39:21.425 line:95%,end
Between the costume fiasco
and the scratched CD,

00:39:21.492 --> 00:39:22.827 line:95%,end
I've had it with her antics.

00:39:22.893 --> 00:39:25.196 line:95%,end
Abby, can I talk to you for a second

00:39:25.262 --> 00:39:27.098 line:95%,end
I just wanted to see--
is it, like, your goal in life

00:39:27.164 --> 00:39:28.666 line:95%,end
to make Paige feel bad?

00:39:28.733 --> 00:39:31.202 line:95%,end
Finally once she had the odd costume

00:39:31.268 --> 00:39:33.404 line:95%,end
and was going to have a second to shine,

00:39:33.471 --> 00:39:34.972 line:95%,end
and then you take it from her.

00:39:35.039 --> 00:39:36.173 line:95%,end
And then you gave her
one that didn't even fit.

00:39:36.240 --> 00:39:37.475 line:95%,end
And it was, like, no big deal.

00:39:37.541 --> 00:39:39.577 line:95%,end
I'm not setting out
to hurt a kid's feelings.

00:39:39.643 --> 00:39:40.978 line:95%,end
You have to understand that.

00:39:41.045 --> 00:39:42.680 line:95%,end
Chloe was the obvious choice.

00:39:42.747 --> 00:39:45.049 line:95%,end
I needed all eyes to go over to her
because she started

00:39:45.116 --> 00:39:46.117 line:95%,end
-with the spoon.
-And I realize that.

00:39:46.183 --> 00:39:47.418 line:95%,end
Kelly, come on.

00:39:47.485 --> 00:39:48.719 line:95%,end
The dance is over.

00:39:48.786 --> 00:39:50.721 line:95%,end
We already did the competition.

00:39:50.788 --> 00:39:52.223 line:95%,end
They were second.

00:39:52.289 --> 00:39:54.024 line:95%,end
Who cares about the dress?

00:39:54.091 --> 00:39:56.994 line:95%,end
God forbid you would see Paige
stand out just a little bit.

00:39:57.061 --> 00:39:59.430 line:95%,end
ABBY: There's five kids.
You can see them all on stage.

00:39:59.497 --> 00:40:00.364 line:95%,end
Whatever, Abby.

00:40:00.431 --> 00:40:02.333 line:95%,end
I mean, it's something
different every day.

00:40:03.401 --> 00:40:04.235 line:95%,end
That's it.

00:40:04.301 --> 00:40:06.871 line:95%,end
I will not take these accusations

00:40:06.937 --> 00:40:08.873 line:95%,end
<i>and finger pointing, anymore.</i>

00:40:08.939 --> 00:40:10.007 line:95%,end
I've had it.

00:40:10.074 --> 00:40:13.811 line:95%,end
Girls, every single one of you know

00:40:13.878 --> 00:40:17.615 line:95%,end
the reason we change things
is because it doesn't look right.

00:40:17.681 --> 00:40:19.583 line:95%,end
That's why we change routines.

00:40:19.650 --> 00:40:22.586 line:95%,end
Don't go accusing people of doing things

00:40:22.653 --> 00:40:23.687 line:95%,end
that they didn't do.

00:40:23.754 --> 00:40:26.490 line:95%,end
Win or lose, I'm not going
to send somebody out there

00:40:26.557 --> 00:40:28.025 line:95%,end
with bad music.

00:40:28.092 --> 00:40:29.927 line:95%,end
And if any one of your mothers
have something to say about it,

00:40:29.994 --> 00:40:31.762 line:5%,start
come to Abby and find out

00:40:31.829 --> 00:40:33.898 line:5%,start
what happens with the CD when it skips.

00:40:33.964 --> 00:40:36.267 line:5%,start
And we'll tell you exactly
what to do with it.

00:40:44.842 --> 00:40:46.944 line:5%,start
MELISSA: Come on, girls.
We're getting on the bus.

00:40:47.611 --> 00:40:50.514 line:5%,start
Finally, Abby has put an end
to the CD skipping issue.

00:40:50.581 --> 00:40:52.049 line:5%,start
<i>We both said our piece.</i>

00:40:52.116 --> 00:40:54.552 line:5%,start
<i>And if the moms don't believe it,</i>
<i>that's their problem.</i>

00:40:54.618 --> 00:40:56.387 line:5%,start
I'm not discussing it anymore.

